	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think both FM and PCM have their own individual strengths and weaknesses. If given to the right composer, both SNES and Genesis can produce awesome music. FM however has the problem that it's VERY EASY to screw up. Many lesser tunes on the Genesis sound bad because the instruments are distorted. This is the result of a lazy composer, unwilling to spend the time which is needed to deliberately fine-tune the parameters.
<br />
<br />If there is one company which could handle practically every sound chip very well, it's Konami.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


